about.summary: Collection of conversion, analytical, geodesic, mapping, and plotting functions. Used to support packages and code written by researchers at the Southwest Fisheries Science Center of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration.

name: r-swfscmisc
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.3' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-swfscmisc
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/swfscMisc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/swfscMisc/swfscMisc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3ab4a4b4a2af18fe5b937a91eb6e64dda7f237939bc8ca9d2fc5bdcb62969f0f

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-ggrepel
    - r-magrittr
    - r-mapdata
    - r-maps
    - r-reshape2
    - r-rlang
    - r-spatstat
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-ggrepel
    - r-magrittr
    - r-mapdata
    - r-maps
    - r-reshape2
    - r-rlang
    - r-spatstat
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('swfscMisc')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('swfscMisc')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/EricArcher/swfscMisc
  license: GPL-2
  summary: Collection of conversion, analytical, geodesic, mapping, and plotting functions. Used
    to support packages and code written by researchers at the Southwest Fisheries Science
    Center of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - nick-youngblut

# Package: swfscMisc
# Type: Package
# Title: Miscellaneous Functions for Southwest Fisheries Science Center
# Description: Collection of conversion, analytical, geodesic, mapping, and plotting functions. Used to support packages and code written by researchers at the Southwest Fisheries Science Center of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration.
